display_get_frequency.example:
```
var _freq = display_get_frequency();

    if (_freq >= 240)
    {
        game_set_speed(240, gamespeed_fps);
    }
    else if (_freq >= 120)
    {
        game_set_speed(120, gamespeed_fps);
    }
    else if (_freq >= 60)
    {
        game_set_speed(60, gamespeed_fps);
    }
    else
    {
        game_set_speed(30, gamespeed_fps);
    }

```
The above code gets the frequency of the display, and runs some conditions to set the game running at 240, 120, 60 or 30 fps. This means that if your display is 90hz the game will run at 60 fps, if it's 144hz then it will run at 120 fps, etc. Of course, you can pass the frequency of the display directly into  [game_set_speed()](https://manual.yoyogames.com/GameMaker_Language/GML_Reference/General_Game_Control/game_set_speed.htm) so it's used as the game's frame rate.

