matrix_build_projection_ortho.description:
This function builds an orthographic projection matrix based on the specified parameters listed below (this is the default projection method used when you create a room in GameMaker Studio 2 without changing anything). Sometimes you need to switch
    from a perspective projection to an orthographic projection which is what this function is for. It is typically used to draw an overlay, for example, to show the score or other aspects as this gives a "flat" view of the elements drawn (ie:
    no perspective) in a 3D game. See the image below to get an idea of the difference between orthographic and perspective views.

